There seems to be growing tension between Britain and the European Union over the supply of vaccines. European Commission president Ursula von der Leyen has threatened to stop the export of doses from Europe to Britain. #eNCA​ Courtesy #DStv403 LONDON - President Cyril Ramaphosa has been invited by British Prime Minister Boris Johnson to attend the G7 summit. Australia, India, South Korea and America will be part of the June summit. READ: Ramaphosa urges G7 to support Africa's development eNCA's UK correspondent Olly Barratt says Johnson invited Ramaphosa because of his key role in the battle against COVID-19.